snippet.textDisplay: Well... Just yesterday I... Uh... Had a very gore-containing dream... When I fell asleep during the Afternoon as usual I had a dream about another Adventure Time Dream and it was where there were to Finns that had to go next to off themselves so they went to this barrier that looked all blocky like the Earlier Alpha Version of Minecraft with a bright blue sky. One digs a whole and the other one barries the other one and they have their heads together. And then something ignites between the two of a lethal explosion that kills the one Finn on the bottom INSTANTLY blowing up their whole entire bottom gruesomely which I didn’t see in my second/third point view dream while I saw the other one crying with blood from their hair and I didn’t see much of the blond hair like you guys would expect on the later on seasons and it looked like that Finn on the top of the buried grass just looked really sad and almost paralyzed and shocked on that explosion that killed the Finn on the bottom. He looked like he was going to presumably die as well. But god my dreams feel so weirdly messed up when I think about fictional characters into these slightly more violent settings without even looking at the types of videos to remind me of the dreams that would be more parallel to them. Although, I did have a dream where I was in a first person view of Finn Mertens fighting some TF2 Zombies and brutually killing them and eventually meeting up with Marceline and he talked about how Marceline his former love interest having romantic feelings towards Princess Bubblegum made her soft which Marceline laughed very hysterically and in a sarcastic type of way. She sighed while Finn just felt like something was going to happen with the possible prediction I have that I think Marceline was going to either violently punches Finn and presumably beats the hell out him for the thought of having about what Finn said come off as a homophobic that Finn said out of jealousy, or just with Finn asking why she laughed or Marceline leaving Finn with a happy sigh rolling her eyes. It’s weird because some of these dreams people rarely think about but are like wow that reminds me of this or that.
